The story revolves around "Mob," a boy who will explode if his emotional capacity reaches 100%. This boy with psychic powers earned his nickname "Mob" because he does not stand out among other people. He keeps his psychic powers bottled up so he can live normally, but if his emotional level reaches 100, something will overwhelm his entire body.
(Source: Anime News Network)

Dororo, a young orphan thief, meets Hyakkimaru, a powerful ronin. Hyakkimaru's father, a greedy feudal lord, had made a pact with 12 demons, offering his yet-unborn son's body parts in exchange for great power. Thus, Hyakkimaru - who was born without arms, legs, eyes, ears, a nose or a mouth - was abandoned in a river as a baby. Rescued and raised by Dr. Honma, who equips him with artificial limbs and teaches him sword-fighting techniques, Hyakkimaru discovers that each time he slays a demon, a piece of his body is restored. Now, he roams the war-torn countryside in search of demons.
Ao no Outline: Tensai no Egaku Sekai wo Bonjin ga Nurikaeru Houhou

"Fascinating" "Overwhelming" "Addictive" "Captivating"
Those are the reactions when people see her paintings.
As a high school student and aspiring artist, I desperately wanted to paint like her.
Yuri Kashiwazaki, the girl who is regarded a "genius," no matter what she draws.

"I just came by to see you. I only paint when I want to."

She is my childhood friend, at once the closest and furthest person to me. One day, she just stopped painting, but I remained in her shadow and continued to wield my paintbrush.

"I'm going to keep painting. I won't give up. I won't use talent as an excuse."

Until the day when Yuri starts painting again. Until the day she will admire my paintings.

This is the story of an ordinary boy who devotes his youth to art, to challenge a "genius."

(Source: Fantasia Bunko, translated)
Youkya na Kanojo wa Kyorikan ga Bugtteiru

Ayano Sasagawa is the unattainable flower of the class. When I rescued her from being propositioned, I suddenly found myself with her full attention...

"Thank you, Fujimura."

I was surprised to find that she even knew my name! After that, she became strangely fond of me and started hanging out with me all the time......! She brought me home on weekends and holidays, fishing for compliments as if she were a child, and even sleeping over. I was supposed to be enjoying my life as an introverted loner, but then I realized that her presence had already become a part of my daily life.......

"Are you coming over today?"
"Just you? So I'll have you all to myself!"
"......does that mean you think I'm special?"

He thought she was from another world, but now she is zero distance away.
This is a youth caste love comedy, where you are at the mercy of a girl who is too bold!

(Source: Fantasia Bunko, translated)
